'''Automated flight following''' (AFF) is [[GPS Aircraft Tracking|GPS aircraft tracking]] that is mandated by a government agency (or other governing body) for its contractors.<ref>http://www.guardianmobility.com/automated-flight-following/</ref> The following criteria must be met:
* The device must transmit position reports every two minutes * The position reports must be pushed into the third-party database (where they are automatically tracked by dispatchers<ref>https://www.aff.gov/</ref>)
Common uses for AFF devices are contractors flying for [[USDA]] during fire season and contractors flying for utility companies.
