{{Politics of Malta}} The '''Cabinet of Malta''' is the collective decision-making body of the [[Government of Malta]], composed of the [[Prime Minister of Malta|Prime Minister]] and a number of Ministers who are selected by the Prime Minister from the elected members of [[House of Representatives of Malta|House of Representatives]] to head government departments. [[Parliamentary Secretaries]] (equivalent to junior ministers) can also be invited to attend cabinet meetings as well as other senior government officials. It is presided over by the Prime Minister of Malta.
