{{Politics of Abia State}}

The '''Judiciary of Abia State''' is a branch of the [[Abia State Government]] that interpretes and applies the laws of [[Abia State]]. It acts as a mechanism for [[dispute resolution]] and also ensure [[equal justice under law]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lawnigeria.com/Judicature/State%20Judicature%20and%20Judiciary/AbiaStateJudicature.html|title=Abia State Judiciary|publisher=Law Nigeria|accessdate=6 October 2015}}</ref>

==Structure==
The Judiciary consists of the [[Abia State High Court of Justice|High Court]] with 23 serving Judges, [[Customary Court of Appeal]] with 4 Judges, [[Magistrate's court]]s with 56 Magistrates and [[Customary court]]s all headed by [[Judge]]s and [[Magistrate]]s. The [[Chief Judge of Abia State|Chief Judge]], appointed by the [[Governor of Abia State|Governor]] sequel to approval by the [[Abia State House of Assembly|House of Assembly]] is the head of the Judiciary.

