'''Mulenge''' is a city of the [[Kigoma]] group in [[Uvira]] Territory, [[South Kivu]], [[Democratic Republic of Congo]]. It is located on the highlands overlooking the town of Uvira.

The town's name gave rise to the term ''[[Banyamulenge]]'', literally "people of Mulenge", a name for the mainly Tutsi [[Kinyarwanda]] speakers resident in South Kivu.

