'''White Ivorians''' are those who were born in or reside in [[Ivory Coast]], who descend from [[Europe]]. There was a small but prominent [[White people|white]] [[French people|French]] community in Ivory Coast until 2002, when a [[First Ivorian Civil War|failed coup d'état and civil war]] led to [[2004 French–Ivorian clashes|anti-European and French riots and attacks on white persons]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|title = Hearts heavy, whites feeling driven from Africa|url = http://www.csmonitor.com/2003/0227/p01s03-woaf.html|newspaper = Christian Science Monitor|access-date = 2015-09-02|issn = 0882-7729|first = Danna|last = Harman}}</ref> Of the 20,000 living in the country at the start of the conflict, by 2004 only 15,000 remained.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|title = French fears in Ivory Coast|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/3410953.stm|newspaper = BBC|date = 2004-01-19|access-date = 2015-09-02}}</ref>
