[[File:Árpád emlékmű Ópusztaszer3.JPG|thumb|Monument of [[List of rulers of Hungary|Hungarian Grand Prince]] [[Árpád]]]]

The '''Ópusztaszer National Heritage Park''' is an [[open-air museum]] of [[Hungarian history]] in [[Ópusztaszer]], [[Hungary]]. It was established in 1982 and is most famous for being the location of the [[Arrival of the Hungarians|Feszty Panorama]], a [[cyclorama]]  by  [[Árpád Feszty]] and his assistants, depicting the beginning of the [[Hungarian conquest of the Carpathian Basin]] in 895. The painting was completed in 1894 for the 1000th anniversary of the event.<ref name= "MagyarSzo p. 19">{{harvnb|MagyarSzo|2008|p=19}}</ref><ref name="itthon.hu">{{cite web |date= 2010 |url = http://itthon.hu/site/upload/mtrt/kiadvanyok/puszta/english/05.html|title = The Puszta and Lake Tisza|format = |publisher = Tourism portal of Hungary| accessdate = January 6, 2010 | last= |quote=}}</ref> 
[[File:Ópusztaszer rotunda.jpg|thumb|180px|Rotunda in Ópusztaszer; the location of the Feszty Panorama]]
In the 1970s, a decision was made to build a heritage park in [[Csongrád County]]. Restoration of the ''[[Arrival of the Hungarians]]'' painting and the construction of a new [[Rotunda (architecture)|rotunda]] for the cyclorama began. Construction stopped in 1979 and parts of the canvas were again stored rolled up. In 1991, a Polish group of restorers won the contract for a new restoration.<ref name="magyarmuzeum.org">{{cite web |date= 2010 |url = http://magyarmuzeum.org/index.php?projectid=4&menuid=368#534|title =The Feszty Panorama Painting |format = |publisher = magyarmuzeum.org| accessdate = January 9, 2010 | last=Kerkay, Emese  |quote=}}</ref>  Since 1995 it has been on display again, together with artificial terrain and hidden speakers playing sound effects. It is the main attraction of the heritage park of Ópusztaszer.

